- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the All-Path protocols are distributed switching protocols. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper discusses the advantages of different protocols depending on the type of traffic. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possibility as the paper may touch on security concerns related to routing protocols. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category, but the paper does mention analytical and simulation-based load balancing capabilities, which could potentially fall under this category.
